</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,151,249]" pageId="7" pageNumber="282">
Described from a single male taken on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Webb" authorityYear="1841" box="[594,778,151,177]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Tamaricaceae" genus="Tamarix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="anglica">
<emphasis box="[594,778,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="282">Tamarix anglica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the 
<collectingRegion box="[856,1026,151,177]" country="Spain" name="Canarias" pageId="7" pageNumber="282">Canary Islands</collectingRegion>
, this remains the only known record of this species (zur Strassen 1966). Recently, the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Priesner" authorityYear="1933" box="[800,978,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Mesandrothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[800,978,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="282">Mesandrothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recalled from synonymy with 
<taxonomicName authority="Priesner, 1928" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Xylaplothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="282">Xylaplothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to include 20 species, including 
<taxonomicName authority="(Mound &amp; Tree 2019)" baseAuthorityName="Mound &amp; Tree" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[634,1205,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Mesandrothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caliginosus">
<emphasis box="[634,947,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="282">Mesandrothrips caliginosus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mound, L. A. &amp; Tree, D. J." box="[961,1197,223,249]" pageId="7" pageNumber="282" pagination="327 - 341" refId="ref5091" refString="Mound, L. A. &amp; Tree, D. J. (2019) Rediagnoses of the Asian genera Xylaplothrips and Mesandrothrips (Thysanoptera, Phlaeothripinae, Haplothripini), with keys to Australian species. Zootaxa, 4613, 327 - 341. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4613.2.6" type="journal article" year="2019">Mound &amp; Tree 2019</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
